Test for #21175:
Complexity: 2

We should cover both path types:
- [x] Windows - @ramya-rao-a 
- [x] MacOS/Linux - **@mjbvz**

We now support to skip or un-skip files via the "Toggle Skipping this file" context menu action on a stack frame for the "legacy" protocol.

Using `"protocol": "legacy"` check:
- If you run "Toggle Skipping this file" on a stack frame, the source file is actually skipped/unskipped according to these [skipping rules](https://code.visualstudio.com/docs/nodejs/nodejs-debugging#_skipping-uninteresting-code-node-chrome).
- Stack frames from skipped files are grayed out in the call stack

If you aren't sure what code to test, use something like this:

a.ts:
```js
import * as b from './b';

function f() {
  console.log('f');
}

b.callback(f);
```

b.ts
```js
export function callback(cb) {
  cb();
}
```

Then you can easily verify that when b.ts is skipped, you can do a step-in to step directly from `b.callback(f)` to `f`.
